  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Pellegrini describes the form of the letters as similar to that \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000513\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000513\u003C/a> and \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000517\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000517\u003C/a>; he also notes that they have been painted in red, although he appears to imply that this was done in modern times, with the praecnomen and the interpunct of line 9 remaining unpainted.\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[216,219,222,225,228,231,234,237],{"id":217,"html":218},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Caium · Valerium · Apollinarem\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"praenomen\" data-text=\"Caium\">C̣(aium)\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"nomen\" data-text=\"Valerium\">Val(erium)\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Apollinarem\">Apollinaṛẹṃ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>v(irum) p(erfectissimum) · corr(ectorem) · prov(inciae) · Ṣịc(iliae) \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ẹxemplum unicuṃ \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ạbstinentiae inte-\u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>g̣ritatis eṭ innoce