terial.stone.marble\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html\">marble\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.statue_base\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.html\">statue base\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">169\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\"/>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\"/>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Pellegrini describes the form of the letters as similar to that \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000513\">ISic000513\u003C/ref> and \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000517\">ISic000517\u003C/ref>; he also notes that they have been painted in red, although he appears to imply that this was done in modern times, with the praecnomen and the interpunct of line 9 remaining unpainted.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462281\">Lilybaeum\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/6542148\">Marsala\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.80355, 12.4379\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0291\" notAfter-custom=\"0314\" evidence=\"prosopography office\">Dated to the period of Diocletian or Constantine, but probably prior to 314 CE, on the basis of the office and titles\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" when=\"1884\">Reported by Pellegrini, in a piece dated 'Trapani, 12 aprile 1886' as 'nella corte della casa Lipari' in Marsala, and as having been found 2 years previously, i.e. c.1884,  'a Lilibeo'.\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"not-observed\" subtype=\"lost\">The piece does not seem to have been observed since, and is either lost or in private hands.\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">None\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n     